It may be called "common," but the common pheasant, native to Asia, is far from ordinary. The males are renowned for their striking plumage, with long and thin tails. Photographer Lin Ge captured some of these beautiful birds in Daqing City, northeast China's Heilongjiang Province. For more photos taken by Lin Ge, check the links below: Wonderful moment of a little tern capturing fish Beautiful photos of flamingos Feast your eyes on brightly colored orange-bellied leafbirds Beautiful photos of fork-tailed sunbirds Red-headed trogon: A brightly colored bird Beautiful moments of bearded reedlings playing in the snow (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)